"tooltiptext" data-text="Yet Another Generic Swerve Library"></template></span></a> Here is our code. We add the vision measurement in swerve subsystem. Do u think it’s going to work</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-21T16:35:27.986Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":20,"readers_count":19,"score":4.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":496449,"topic_slug":"setting-heading-for-sweve","display_username":"Prince","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/OCHS-STEM-Club/2025-CompBot-YAGSL","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - OCHS-STEM-Club/2025-CompBot-YAGSL","clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":19820,"username":"ArchdukeTim","name":"Tim Winters","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/archduketim/{size}/256125_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":57204,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"1792 Lead Programmer"},"post_url":"/t/setting-heading-for-sweve/496449/8","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3564683,"name":"Val","username":"Otter502","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/otter502/{size}/245799_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-21T17:37:14.797Z","cooked":"<p>We usually prefer not to reset our gyro, we just rotate the field offset<br>
since this lets the driver reset their field relative heading easily:</p>
<p>We use limelights to find the field relative angle, then use that to find our gyro’s angle.</p>
<p>In order to change the angle / offset the field relative heading we just rotate the chassis speeds before they get sent to the robot:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">    public static ChassisSpeeds rotateLinearChassisSpeeds(ChassisSpeeds in, Rotation2d offset){
        var modifiedLinear = new Translation2d(
            in.vxMetersPerSecond,
            in.vyMetersPerSecond
        ).rotateBy(offset);

        return new ChassisSpeeds(
            modifiedLinear.getX(),
            modifiedLinear.getY(), 
        in.omegaRadiansPerSecond);
    }
</code></pre>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-21T17:37:14.797Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":15,"readers_count":14,"score":3.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":496449,"topic_slug":"setting-heading-for-sweve","display_username":"Val","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63596,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Programming"},"post_url":"/t/setting-heading-for-sweve/496449/9","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null}],"stream":[3564529,3564537,3564543,3564549,3564569,3564573,3564579,3564581,3564683]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,135]],"suggested_topics":[{"id":471680,"title":"What tool does your team teach to new members for interacting with git?","fancy_title":"What tool does your team teach to new members for interacting with git?","slug":"what-tool-does-your-team-teach-to-new-members-for-interacting-with-git","posts_count":17,"reply_count":5,"highest_post_number":17,"image_url":null,"created_at":"2024-09-23T08:44:37.322Z","last_posted_at":"2024-09-27T11:42:45.668Z","bumped":true,"bumped_at":"2024-09-27T11:42:45.668Z","archetype":"regular","unseen":false,"pinned":false,"unpinned":null,"excerpt":"poll Personally, I use the CLI tool because that’s what I’ve always used and it’s what I use at work, but I’ve met people in professional contexts who 